      "content": "it felt way more physical than just \"intuition\" tho. like it wasn't just a vibe, it was a literal harmonic clash. it was almost like two different notes playing at once in the same voice, but one was slightly off-key. if it's not just my imagination, could there be some kind of biological mechanism for this? like, could the way someone speaks when they're lying actually change the resonance of their vocal cords?",
